[p]A [b]headache[/b] can be described as a pain anywhere in the region of the head or neck. It can be a symptom of a number of different conditions. This occurs in migraines (sharp, or throbbing pains), tension-type headaches, and cluster headaches.[ref to="1" no="1" /][/p]

[p]It is worth noting that due to its lacks of pain receptors, headaches are not caused by pain within the brain tissue itself, instead, headaches are caused by disturbances of the pain-sensitive structures around the brain.[/p]

[p]Headaches are most commonly induced under the influence of heavy dosages of stimulating compounds, such as traditional stimulants, certain [int-link to="/summaries/psychedelics/miscellaneous"]psychedelics[/int-link], and certain [int-link to="/summaries/dissociatives"]dissociatives[/int-link]. This holds particularly true during the offset of the experience and if the person is dehydrated or has not eaten enough food.[/p]
